<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 30 at 6:43AM CDT  by NWS Shreveport</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southern Franklin,
northeastern Wood, northwestern Upshur, southern Titus and Camp
Counties through 715 AM CDT...
At 642 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Quitman, or 11 miles southwest of Winnsboro, moving northeast at 55
mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Mount Pleasant, Pittsburg, Winnsboro, Leesburg, Quitman, Cason,
Scroggins, Pleasant Grove, Newsome, Rocky Mound, Perryville,
Monticello, Roeder and Harvard.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 100 PM CDT for northeastern
Texas.</instruction>
